cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses a modification to the classic RNN structure to improve accuracy and reduce the depth of recursive training procedures in partially observable domains. This falls under the domain of machine learning, making cs.LG the most likely sub-category. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of Artificial Neural Networks to learn useful state representations for high-dimensional visual and continuous control domains. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely sub-category. 
3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper discusses the use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) and General Value Function Networks (GVFNs) to improve accuracy and reduce the depth of recursive training procedures. This falls under the domain of neural computing, making cs.NE a likely sub-category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the use of General Value Function Networks (GVFNs) to facilitate accurate prediction with no gradients needed back-in-time in domains with substantial long-term dependences. This falls under the domain of control systems, making cs.SY a possible sub-category. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper discusses the use of Artificial Neural Networks to learn useful state representations for high-dimensional visual domains. This falls under the domain of computer vision
